subSubSection.paragraph:
Male
. Male of this species can be easily separated from all other species by having large body size (length 10.0–16.5 mm) and postero-lateral corners of S6 and S7 strongly convex (
Fig. 17
). 
Other characters of importance are
: first flagellomere 3.6–4.0 times its width; propodeum with fine weakly noticeable punctures; claws symmetrical without additional tooth; hypopygium narrow apically and strongly widened subbasally (
Fig. 22
); paramere pointed apically (
Fig. 19
); forewing brownish, with distinct apical darker spot from marginal, second and third submarginal and apical half of second discoidal cells to wing apex; pterostigma brown (
Fig. 28
); body mostly black with light yellow spots on: face, gena, T2, T3, S3, S4 and proleg; antenna mostly black (
Fig. 2
).
